{
  "stem": "2067.3",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But that may have been a reason why she willingly and gladly agreed to the plan to try to escape.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It was a very, very dangerous enterprise.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Because we had to travel more than 1,000 miles, crossing four borders.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And all borders were very heavily guarded by that time.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Unlike 1941 when we tried it, now we were in almost a year later.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And things had changed.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we decided on a date-- the 27th of September, 1942.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Our friend, Lex, was the in-between man.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He started contacting that same smuggler in Tilburg, met with him, arranged everything, arranged the amount of money we had to pay-- half to him, half to the other smuggler in Paris, that we would go via Paris-- first via Belgium, then Paris.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And he got 50% in advance.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He would see to it that we would get false Belgian identity cards without the J, of course, with a Gentile Belgian name, Flemish name, which was very similar to the Dutch names.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he would wait on the 27th, which was a Sunday, in Tilburg, with three bicycles.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] The day of our departure, I went out for the first time from my hiding place without, of course, the yellow star, obviously.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Went to my parents.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "My parents in the meantime had also been forced to seek asylum in that same apartment where Dottie was.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I went there and met Dottie, met my parents, said goodbye to my parents.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And Rudolf-- Rudolf Fuyts that was the name of the man where Dottie was hiding out in his house-- he, Dottie, and I left.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "She went first again to a place where she could meet her parents and said goodbye to her parents.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "That was the last time she saw them.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
